lctech f1c200s: wire the MUSB (usb_otg) node to the dedicated-DMA engine

Add dmas/dma-names to usb@1c13000 so sunxi_dma.c (CONFIG_USB_SUNXI_DMA) can
request the DDMA USB DRQ (SUN4I_DMA_DEDICATED 4) for the RX and TX endpoint
FIFO paths. This is the DDMA bank (channels distinct from esp-hosted's SPI
NDMA), so USB and SPI DMA do not share channels.

Depends on patch 0014 (adds the &dma controller node + the sun4i-a10.h
dt-binding include).

Signed-off-by: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>

--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/suniv-f1c100s.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/suniv-f1c100s.dtsi
@@ -145,6 +145,9 @@
 			phy-names = "usb";
 			extcon = <&usbphy 0>;
 			allwinner,sram = <&otg_sram 1>;
+			dmas = <&dma SUN4I_DMA_DEDICATED 4>,
+			       <&dma SUN4I_DMA_DEDICATED 4>;
+			dma-names = "rx", "tx";
 			status = "disabled";
 		};
 
